<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFE5FFCEFF8DFE41FE02FC2E" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE5FFCEFF8DFE41FD52FDCE" blockId="63.[113,1089,423,958]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFF8DFE41FF60FE0E" bold="true" box="[113,222,423,446]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFF1FFE41FE2EFE0E" author="BOHEMAN" box="[227,400,423,446]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" refId="ref47980" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1857: Catalogue of Coleopterous Insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part IX. Cassidae. Printed by Order of the trustees [of the British Museum], London, 225 pp." type="book" year="1857">BOHEMAN (1857)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFE01FE41FD7FFE0E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[509,705,423,446]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tauroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFE01FE41FD7FFE0E" box="[509,705,423,446]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">Tauroma boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from unknown number of specimens and stated ‘Dom. Chevrolat. Mus. Holm.’ as type depository. Latter on, he indicated this taxon as present in his collection (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFE63FE01FDFAFE4E" author="BOHEMAN" box="[415,580,487,510]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN 1862</bibRefCitation>
). I have examined 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFE5FFCEFCECFE01FC10FE4E" box="[784,942,487,510]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
coming from the collection of Chevrolat, one retained by Boheman and the other purchased by Hamlet Clark. I consider them as 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE5FFCEFE86FDC1FE69FD8E" box="[378,471,551,574]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">syntypes</typeStatus>
as both agree with the primary description. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFC5CFDC1FBFFFD8E" author="SPAETH" box="[928,1089,551,574]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" pagination="305 - 314" refId="ref51270" refString="SPAETH F. 1931 a: Uber die Gattung Tauroma Hope (Col.). Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 92: 305 - 314." type="journal article" year="1931" yearSuffix="a">SPAETH (1931a)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFEFBFDA1FE55FDEE" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[263,491,583,606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFEFBFDA1FE55FDEE" box="[263,491,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">Omocerus bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFDD6FDA1FCFBFDEE" authority="Boheman, 1850" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[554,837,583,606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFDD6FDA1FD2AFDEE" box="[554,660,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. reichei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFD60FDA1FCFBFDEE" author="Boheman" box="[668,837,583,606]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" refId="ref47905" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1850: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Primus. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 452 pp. + 4 pls." type="book" year="1850">Boheman, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
assuming that the later is rather variable species and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFE50FD81FD82FDCE" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[428,572,615,638]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFE50FD81FD82FDCE" box="[428,572,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only its form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE5FFCEFF6CFD61FE02FC2E" blockId="63.[113,1089,423,958]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFF6CFD61FE81FD2E" author="BOHEMAN" box="[144,319,647,670]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" refId="ref47905" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1850: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Primus. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 452 pp. + 4 pls." type="book" year="1850">BOHEMAN (1850)</bibRefCitation>
used at least 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFE5FFCEFE3AFD61FDD0FD2E" box="[454,622,647,670]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
for description of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFCD0FD61FC2AFD2E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[812,916,647,670]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFCD0FD61FC2AFD2E" box="[812,916,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as he mentioned 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFE5FFCEFF8DFD41FF64FD0E" box="[113,218,679,702]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" type="generic">three type</specimenCount>
localities. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE5FFCEFEB7FD41FDB2FD0E" author="BOROWIEC" box="[331,524,679,702]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE5FFCEFD7BFD41FD57FD0E" box="[647,745,679,702]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">lectotype</typeStatus>
from the only specimen retained by Boheman from 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFE5FFCEFEC9FD21FE1CFD6E" box="[309,418,711,734]" name="Colombia" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. I have compared this 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE5FFCEFD75FD21FD55FD6E" box="[649,747,711,734]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">lectotype</typeStatus>
to 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE5FFCEFCF5FD21FCD8FD6E" box="[777,870,711,734]" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFC7BFD21FBABFD6E" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[903,1045,711,734]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFC7BFD21FBABFD6E" box="[903,1045,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in my opinion the two taxa are distinct. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFDEAFD01FD47FD4E" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[534,761,743,766]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFDEAFD01FD47FD4E" box="[534,761,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">Omocerus bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has distinctly coarser punctate elytra and punctures with deeper fovea, the postscutellar hump is more prominent and wider, laterally with deeper impressions, and longer humeral projections than 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFCA3FCC1FC79FC8E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[863,967,807,830]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFCA3FCC1FC79FC8E" box="[863,967,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Due to the coarser and deeper punctation the elytra of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFDCEFCA1FD7EFCEE" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[562,704,839,862]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFDCEFCA1FD7EFCEE" box="[562,704,839,862]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears less regular while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE5FFCEFC25FCA1FBFFFCEE" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[985,1089,839,862]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Omocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE5FFCEFC25FCA1FBFFFCEE" box="[985,1089,839,862]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="338">O. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has elytra smooth and surface between punctures regular and smooth. Therefore I restore the species status of 
